message.entry: All sample times for the Constellation Diagram block must be discrete.\nContinuous sample time is not allowed.
The SamplesPerSymbol property must have a positive integer value greater than that of the SampleOffset property.
The SampleOffset property must have a non-negative integer value smaller than that of SamplesPerSymbol property.
The SymbolsToDisplay property must be a positive integer or ''{0}''.
When the Measurements tool is enabled, the SymbolsToDisplay property can not be less than the value of the MeasurementInterval property.
When the Measurements tool is enabled, the number of symbols to display can not be less than the value of the MeasurementInterval property.
When the Measurements tool is enabled, the ReferenceConstellation property must be a vector with numeric values.
The ReferenceConstellation property must be a vector with numeric values.
The average constellation power must be a non-negative numeric value.
The constellation phase offset must be numeric.
The ReferenceColor property must be a vector with three elements, all in the range [0,1].
When SymbolsToDisplay is 'Input frame length' the input frame length must be an integer multiple of the SamplesPerSymbol property.
Markers cannot be disabled in the Constellation Diagram when 'ShowTrajectory' = false.\n
The selected LineStyle is invalid under the current 'ShowTrajectory' value.\n
The selected reference-constellation marker is invalid under the current 'ShowReferenceConstellation' value.\n
To ensure a consistent offset, Constellation Diagram blocks in conditionally executed subsystems need an input length that is an integer multiple of Samples per symbol.
